# Introduction / Overview

### Purpose of the Database

The Expense Tracker database is designed to provide a structured and efficient way to store and manage users’ financial transactions. It enables users to record their income and expenses, organize them into categories, and analize their spending habits overtime. By maintaining clear relationships between users, categories, and individual expenses, the database ensures data integrity, scalability, and ease of reporting. The schema supports key application features such as expense categorization, transaction history, filtering, and summary calculations.

### Scope

This database focuses on three primary entities:

1. **Users \-** Individuals using the application to manage their finances.  
2. **Categories \-** User-defined groups (e.g., “Groceries,” “Rent,” “Entertainment”) for organizing expenses.  
3. **Expenses \-** Individual financial transactions that record amount, type (income or expense), date, and optional category.

The schema emphasizes core features only, ensuring simplicity, scalability, and maintainability for future development.

# Entity-Relationship Diagram (ERD)

### Diagram Description

### Entities

1. Users  
   1. Represents an individual who uses the Expense Tracker  
   2. Each user can own multiple categories and record multiple expenses  
2. Categories  
   1. Represents a label or grouping for related expenses  
   2. Each category belongs to exactly one user  
   3. A category can classify many expenses  
3. Expenses  
   1. Represents a financial transaction, either an income or an expense  
   2. Each expense belongs to exactly one user and may optionally belong to a category

### Relationsips

| Relationship | Entities Involved | Type | Description |
| :---- | :---- | :---- | :---- |
| **Owns** | Users\<-\>Categories | 1:N | A user can own many categories, but each category belongs to only one user. |
| **Records** | Users\<-\>Expenses | 1:N | A user can record many expenses, but each expense is recorded by only one user |
| **Classified\_As** | Categories\<-\>Expenses | 1:N(optional on expense side) | A category can classify many expenses, but an expense may or may not have a category |

# Data Dictionary

## Overview

The data dictionary defines each entity in the Expense Tracker database and provides detailed descriptions of all attributes, their data types, keys, constraints, and purpose.

### Table: Users

| Field name | Data Type | Key | Null | Description / Constraints |
| :---- | :---- | :---- | :---- | :---- |
| id | INT/UUID | PK | No | Unique identifier for each user |
| email | VARCHAR(250) | UNIQUE | No | Users email address, must be unique |
| pasword\_hash | TEXT |  | No | Hashed password for secure authentication |
| display\_name | VARCHAR(250) |  | Yes | Optional display name for the user |
| created\_at | TIMESTAMP |  | No | Timestamp of when the user was created |
| updated\_at | TIMESTAMP |  | No | Timestamp of last update to the record |

**Notes:**

* Each user can have multiple categories and expenses  
* Deleting a user will cascade delete related categories and expenses

### 

### Table: Categories

| Field name | Data Type | Key | Null | Description / Constraints |
| :---- | :---- | :---- | :---- | :---- |
| id | INT/UUID | PK | No | Unique identifier for each category |
| user\_id | INT/UUID | FK-\>Users.id | No | Identifies the user who owns this category |
| name | VARCHAR(250) |  | No | Category name |
| color\_hex | CHAR(7) |  | Yes | Optional color code for UI visualization |
| icon\_key | VARCHAR(50) |  | Yes | Optional icon identifier for UI |
| created\_at | TIMESTAMP |  | No | Timestamp of category creation |
| updated\_at | TIMESTAMP |  | No | Timestamp of lat modification |

**Notes:**

* Each category belongs to one user  
* Each category can classify many expenses  
* (user\_id, name) combination must be unique

### Table: expenses

| Field name | Data Type | Key | Null | Description / Constraints |
| :---- | :---- | :---- | :---- | :---- |
| id | INT/UUID | PK | No | Unique identifier for each expense |
| user\_id | INT/UUID | FK-\>Users.id | No | Identifies the user who recorded the expense |
| category\_id | INT/UUID | FK-\> Categories.id | Yes | Identifies the category this expense belongs to (nullable) |
| txn\_type | VARCHAR(10) |  | No | Defines transaction type |
| amount\_cents | BIGINT |  | No | Translation amount in cents (avoids rounding errors) |
| currency\_code | CHAR(3) |  | No | Currency code (default ‘USD’) |
| txn\_date | DATE |  | No | The date the transaction occured |
| merchant | VARCHAR(250) |  | yes | Optional merchant |
| note | TEXT |  | Yes | Optional note or description |
| created\_at | TIMESTAMP |  | No | Timestamp of record creation |
| updated\_at | TIMESTAMP |  | No | Timestamp of last update |

**Notes:**

* Each expense bolongs to one user and optionally one category  
* Txn type restricted to ‘income’ or ‘expense’  
* Deleting a category sets its linked category\_id to NULL  
* Deleting a user cascades deletion of all their expenses

# Logical Schema

## Overview

	The logical Schema defines the exact SQ:L statements to be used to create the Expense Tracker database tables, establish relationships, and enforce constraints.

### Create Tables

CREATE DATABASE IF NOT EXISTS expense\_tracker  
USE expense\_tracker

\-*\-Users*  
CREATE TABLE users (  
	id 			BIGINT UNSIGNED NOT NULL AUTO\_INCREMENT,  
	email			VARCHAR(250) NOT NULL,  
Password\_hash	TEXT NOT NULL,  
display\_name		VARCHAR(250)  
created\_at		DATETIME NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT\_TIMESTAMP,  
updated\_at    		DATETIME NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT\_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT\_TIMESTAMP,  
	PRIMARY KEY (id),  
)

*\--Categories*  
CREATE TABLE categories (  
id 			BIGINT UNSIGNED NOT NULL AUTO\_INCREMENT,  
user\_id		BIGINT UNSIGNED NOT NULL,  
name			VARCHAR(250) NOT NULL,  
color\_hex		CHAR(7),  
Icon\_key		VARCHAR(50),  
	created\_at		DATETIME NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT\_TIMESTAMP,  
updated\_at    		DATETIME NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT\_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT\_TIMESTAMP,  
PRIMARY KEY (id),  
CONSTRAINT fk\_categories\_user  
     FOREIGN KEY (user\_id) REFERENCES (user\_id, name)  
     ON DELETE CASCADE,  
)

*\--Expenses*  
CREATE TABLE expenses (  
	id 			BIGINT UNSIGNED NOT NULL AUTO\_INCREMENT,  
user\_id		BIGINT UNSIGNED NOT NULL,  
category\_id		BIGINT UNSIGNED NOT NULL,  
txn\_type		ENUM(‘income’ , ‘expense’) NOT NULL,  
amount\_cents	BIGINT UNSIGNED NOT NULL,  
txn\_date		DATE NOT NULL,  
merchant		VARCHAR(250),  
note			TEXT,  
created\_at		DATETIME NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT\_TIMESTAMP,  
updated\_at    		DATETIME NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT\_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT\_TIMESTAMP,  
PRIMARY KEY (id),  
CONSTRAINT fk\_expenses\_user  
      FOREIGN KEY (user\_id) REFERENCES users(id)  
      ON DELETE CASCADE,  
CONSTRAINT fk\_expenses\_category  
      FOREIGN KEY (category\_id) REFERENCES categories(id)  
      ON DELETE SET NULL,  
)
